TY  - JOUR
T1  - Necessary Evils and Interpersonal Sensitivity in Organizations
AU  - Molinsky, Andrew
AU  - Margolis, Joshua
Y1  - 2005/04/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2005.16387884
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2005.16387884
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 245
EP  - 268
VL  - 30
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In order to produce a beneficial result, professionals must sometimes cause harm to another human being. To capture this phenomenon, we introduce the construct of ?necessary evils? and explore the inherent challenges such tasks pose for those who must perform them. Whereas previous research has established the importance of treating victims of necessary evils with interpersonal sensitivity, we focus on the challenges performers face when attempting to achieve this prescribed standard in practice.
AB  - In order to produce a beneficial result, professionals must sometimes cause harm to another human being. To capture this phenomenon, we introduce the construct of ?necessary evils? and explore the inherent challenges such tasks pose for those who must perform them. Whereas previous research has established the importance of treating victims of necessary evils with interpersonal sensitivity, we focus on the challenges performers face when attempting to achieve this prescribed standard in practice.
